HEADWORD: Novene
<hw>No"vene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>novenus</ets>
nine each, in LL., ninth, fr. L. <ets>novem</ets> nine.]</ety>
<def>Relating to, or dependent on, the number nine; novenary.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The triple and <qex>novene</qex> division ran throughout.</q>
